<h1>From Philippe Jean Joseph Lagau</h1>
<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		<td class="salutationRight"> Hambourg ce 4 Avril 1783<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Jai reu la lettre dont Votre Excellence a bien voul mhonorer le 21 du mois pass.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> La prsente lui sera remise par Monsieur Hardouin negociant au Havre de Grace qui a eu lhonneur de faire la Cooissance de Monsieur votre fils en cette ville et qui est en tat de vous en donner de bonnes nouvelles.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> Il ma pri de Le recommender  vos bonts, et comme Il part de ce pas y regrett de tous ceux qui Ly ont conn je prends la libert de vous supplier de daigner Lhonorer de votre bienveillance et de Lacuillir favorablement. Je saisirai toujours avec empressement toute occasion que se prsentera pour vous temoigner ma recooissance ainsi que Le profond respect avec lequel jai Lhonneur dtre / Monsieur / de Votre Excellence / Le trs humble et trs / obeissant Serviteur</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Lagau</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="translation">
<h2><span class="hi-all-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps; text-transform: lowercase;">Translation</span></h2>
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Hamburg, 4 April 1783<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I have received the letter of 21 March with which your excellency honored me.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> The present letter will be delivered to you by Mr. Hardouin, a merchant of Havre de Grace who had the honor of meeting your son in this town and who will be able to give you good news of him.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> He asked me to commend him to your good offices, and as he is leaving the country, much to the regret of all who knew him here, I take the liberty of begging you to honor him with your goodwill and to receive him favorably. I shall always seize eagerly on any occasion that arises to demonstrate my gratitude, together with the profound respect with which I have the honor to be, sir, your excellencys very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Lagau</p>
</div>
</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0386">[386<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0386.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-sn">
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</p>
</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p>The firm of Parish &amp; Thomson also wrote on 4 April (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>) to inform <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> that <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> was still at Hamburg but would proceed overland to The Hague. In the letter, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s of 19 and 24 March were mentioned, for which see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0211" class="document">the firms letter of 7 March</a>, and notes 1 and 2, above.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>Probably <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s of 24 March thanking Lagau for his assistance in tracking <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr>, <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Formerly, Adams Papers, Microfilms. The corpus of the Adams Papers, 16391889, as published on microfilm by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 19541959, in 608 reels. Cited in the present work, when necessary, by reel number. Available in research libraries throughout the United States and in a few libraries in Canada, Europe, and New Zealand.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">APM</span> Reel 108).</p>
</div>
        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0243-fn-0003">3</a>
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> introduced the otherwise unidentified Hardouin in <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-05-02-0079" class="document">a 6 May letter to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr></a>, describing him as a French young Gentleman whose company I had the pleasure of from Hamborough to Amsterdam, and who intends to go to Havre de Grce to form an establishment in the commercial way (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Adams Family Correspondence&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. H. Butterfield, Marc Friedlaender, Richard Alan Ryerson, Margaret A. Hogan, and others, Cambridge, 1963. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">AFC</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-05-02-0078%20ADMS-print-04-05-02-0079#ADMS-04-05-02-pb-0150" class="pageNo">5:150</a>).</p>
</div>
</div>
